reviews.review_text: Fall in Hartford Good show from start to finish.Like the Loser and I Need A Miracle>Mighty Swell in 1st set.In the 2nd set the Throwin Stones>Not Fade Away>Lovelight rock the house!!Sound is very good,give it a whirl!!

Prefer Prefer this version due to it has the entire rhythm devils and space. For years I looked for this show in it's entirety. I thought for sure all the masters were cut. I love the sound on this one also taper did a great job finding location here .5 stars because it has good sound and is the entire show.

Longest Show of the 80's Great job to Charlie Miller for making this show complete. For an audience recording it sounds very good. In my humble opinion the show is full of energy with not many mistakes made by the band.

a fun listen but  Very sweet recording and the show is long with some nice moments... a commenter below says that there are not many mistakes by the band, but the first set has numerous cacophonous moments such as Greatest Story totally falling apart towards the end and the Jerry barely remembering how to play Dire Wolf and Might As Well. Decent front end of set 2, Estimated full of trippy vibrato effects, good Eyes with jam

Fall '84 N7 High energy psychedelic rock and roll. Big Healy presence, throughout, no doubt contributes. Sloppy at times, which is par for the course, in '84, but it's fun, mostly together, even if in a sometimes nauseating roller coaster type of way.   Audio quality is hit and miss, better at various points, Tinny sounding at first, but then seems to settle into some excellent audio sound.  LONG show. All in all, this Hartford 2-night run is really good and I think it's up there with the Augusta stint from a few nights prior. These China Dolls kill me.
